The paper deals with a problem in probability theory and its applications in computer science, specifically in sketching algorithms, approximation algorithms, parallel repetition, and cryptography. The paper also introduces a new problem called "constrained agreement" which has implications in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and its applications. Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
